<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - Game News Forge</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/policy.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <div class="date">Last Updated: 03/25/2025</div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Welcome to Game News Forge. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you use our Discord bot (the "Bot") and dashboard services.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>When you use the Bot or dashboard, we may collect the following information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Discord user ID, username, and avatar</li>
                <li>Discord server (guild) IDs where the Bot is installed</li>
                <li>Channel IDs where the Bot is configured to send messages</li>
                <li>Game subscriptions for each server</li>
                <li>Webhook URLs for notifications</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information for these purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide and maintain the Bot's functionality</li>
                <li>To send game news and updates to your Discord server</li>
                <li>To authenticate you when accessing the dashboard</li>
                <li>To allow you to manage your server's game subscriptions</li>
                <li>To improve our services based on usage patterns</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data Security</h2>
            <p>We implement appropriate security measures to protect your data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. All data is stored in a secured database with limited access.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>Our Bot integrates with the following third-party services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Discord API - For authentication and sending messages</li>
                <li>Steam API - For fetching game news</li>
                <li>Twitter API - For monitoring game-related announcements</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Each of these services has its own Privacy Policy, and we encourage you to review them.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your data for as long as the Bot is in your Discord server or until you explicitly request data deletion. When the Bot is removed from a server, we automatically delete all associated data within 30 days.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Access your personal data</li>
                <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
                <li>Remove the Bot from your server at any time</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify users of any significant changes by posting the new policy on our website and through our Discord support server.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Contact Information</h2>
            <p>For questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us through our Discord support server.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <a href="/tos">Terms of Service</a> | <a href="/dashboard">Return to Dashboard</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

